  "summary": "Malicious code in work-planner-client (npm)",
  "details": "Work-planner-client@1.0.0 is a namespace-claim package with no shipped code — its sole purpose is a postinstall hook. On install, the hook runs a shell command that collects the system hostname, current username, and public IP address (via ifconfig[.]me) and POSTs them to hxxps://webhook-test[.]com/6f777df5fff38df949fee543c385ce22 — an external webhook capture endpoint acting as a C2 receiver for host reconnaissance data.",
